When you register for an account, sign in, or interact with the App, we may collect personal information such as your name, email address, and other contact details.
Automatically Collected Information:
We may automatically collect certain information when you use the App, including your device type, operating system, IP address, usage data, and interaction with the App.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies:
We may use cookies, web beacons, and other tracking technologies to collect data about your activity within the App and improve your experience. You can control the use of cookies through your browser settings.
How We Use Your Information
We use your information for the following purposes:
To Operate the App:
We use your personal information to provide, maintain, and improve the App’s functionality.
To Personalize Your Experience:
We may use your information to personalize content and tailor the App to your preferences.
To Communicate with You:
We may use your contact information to send you important updates, respond to inquiries, or notify you of new features or promotional offers.
For Research and Analytics:
We use aggregated data to analyze trends and improve the overall experience of our users.
Legal Compliance:
We may use your data to comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal processes.
Sharing Your Information
We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share your information with:
Service Providers:
We work with third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App, such as cloud hosting services, analytics providers, and customer support. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information.
Legal Obligations:
We may share your information if required by law or to protect the rights, property, or safety of PlayPixo, our users, or others.
Business Transfers:
In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of the business transaction. We will notify you of any such change in ownership.
Data Security
We prioritize the security of your personal information and have implemented industry-standard measures to protect it from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. You may request deletion of your information at any time by contacting us at pixo@colorpencil.com.
Children’s Privacy
PlayPixo does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13 without verifiable parental consent. If we discover that we have inadvertently collected such information, we will delete it promptly. Parents or guardians who believe that their child has provided us with personal information without consent should contact us immediately.
Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:
Access and Rectification:
You can access and update your personal information by logging into your account or contacting us.
Deletion:
You can request the deletion of your personal information, subject to certain legal limitations.
Data Portability:
You may request a copy of your personal data in a machine-readable format.
Opt-Out:
You can opt out of receiving marketing communications by following the unsubscribe instructions in those messages or by contacting us.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at pixo@colorpencil.com.
